      <procstep>
        <procdesc>ArcMap was used to edit the source shape files and delete the values in any columns containing Chinese characters, then the ArcGIS 9.2 Feature Class to Feature Class tool was used to move the geographic shapes into SDE.  Microsoft Access was used to import the CHGIS-provided text file containing the properly encoded attribute values.  A new text file containing just attributes with Chinese characters was created with the proper encoding, either GBK or UTF-8 depending on the source.  This text file was imported to a new table in Oracle using SQLLoader with the NLS_CHARACTERSET property set to either UTF8 or ZHS16GBK.  The attributes were then joined back to the shapes using Windows SQLPlus with the NLS_LANGUAGE property set to Traditional Chinese.  This process ensured that the encoding was properly interpreted during the import.</procdesc>
